            <h5>Metropolia</h5>
            <h2>Redesigning and building a website to attract new applicants</h2>
            <img class="hero" src="dimu.svg">
                <div class="summary">
                    <h6>Summary</h6>
                    <p>Digital Design promotional site is an annually updated page to give people interested in the study field a possibility to get to know it better. The redesign process was part of our first-year studies as the very first project assignment.</p>
                </div>
                    <div class="infos">
                        <div class="role">
                            <h6>Role</h6>
                            <p>Front-End Developer (HTML/CSS)</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="timeline">
                            <h6>Timeline</h6>
                            <p>2 months</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tools">
                            <h6>Tools</h6>
                            <p>Figma<br>Visual Studio Code</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                <div class="overview">
                    <h6>Overview</h6>
                    <p>The Digital Design promotional site is an in-depth source to get to know the study program better. The site provides information both about the enrollment process and the studies.<br><br>Although informative, the previous website lacked an appealing design that would have truly captured the attention of interested applicants and had some problems with usability. Our goal was to make the site more visually appealing, easier to navigate and to ensure all key information was simple to find.<br><br>My role focused on building the front-end structure and ensuring that the visual design translated seamlessly from prototype to browser.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="challenge">
                    <h6>The Challenge</h6>
                    <p>The main challenge was to create a design that is both visually appealing and functional, ensuring that prospective students can easily find the information they need about the Digital Design program. Additionally, we needed to ensure that the site is mobile-responsive, catering to a diverse audience with varying levels of technical proficiency. Balancing aesthetics with usability was a key focus throughout the redesign process.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="process">
                    <h6>The Process</h6>
                    <p>In the beginning of the design process, we conducted a questionnaire to current students. Our aim was to find out how the user experience was with the previous page. Through the answers, we found out that most people found the existing page easy to navigate but wanted more information about the studies and working after the degree. Thus, we added a page for frequently asked questions and a video interviewing current students about their views on the degree.
                    </p>
                    <p>We analyzed the existing infosite to identify usability issues and areas for improvement. Based on these insights, we created user personas and use cases to guide our design decisions.
                    </p>
                    <div class="process-full-img">
                        <img src="dimu.png" alt="Process overview">
                    </div>
                    <p>After getting feedback from the client, we chose to go with a brutalist style. Bold colors and big fonts combined with old computer hardware references gave the page a fresh look.</p>
                    <div class="process-full-img">
                        <img src="dimu assets2.svg" alt="Process overview">
                    </div>
                    <p>We then developed wireframes and interactive prototypes, focusing on a clean layout, intuitive navigation, and engaging visuals. We conducted usability testing with a sample of users to gather feedback and iterated on the design accordingly. Finally, we implemented the new design using HTML and CSS, ensuring it is mobile-responsive.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="outcome">
                    <h6>The Outcome</h6>
                    <p>The redesigned Digital Design promotional site successfully combines a visually appealing design with enhanced usability. The new layout features clear navigation, engaging visuals, and comprehensive information about the program, making it easier for prospective students to explore and understand what Digital Design has to offer. The site is fully mobile-responsive, ensuring a seamless experience across all devices. Overall, the redesign has received positive feedback from users, indicating that it effectively meets the needs of its target audience.<br><br>The code files can be viewed <a href="https://github.com/aikaam/Digitaalinen-muotoilu" target="_blank">here.</a></p>
                </div>
